field, . This is related to the fact that field potential
falls out of the equation of state in case of the tachyon field. It should also be noted
that evolution equation for tachyon field contains the logarithmic derivative of the potential.
DYNAMICS OF TACHYONIC INFLATION IN FRW COSMOLOGY 
The tachyon potential  as  but its exact form
is not know at present. Sen has argued that the qualitative dynamics of string theory tachyons can be described by () with
 exponential potential. Padmanabhan went further to
suggest that one can construct a phenomenological runaway potential with the tachyonic equation of state
capable of leading  to a desired cosmology, see also Ref on the similar theme. In what follows we shall consider () with the exponential potential
in purely phenomenological context without claiming any identification of  with the string tachyon field.
Indeed, there are problems with inflation in case the origin of  is traced in string theory and we will
come back to this point later.
